the well-being of others. It recognizes that intelligence is not solely focused on achieving personal goals but extends to nurturing and supporting the happiness and flourishing of others.</p><p>Similarly, the Axiology of Love system explores different facets of love, including love as a choice, emotion, virtue, and skill. Love, in its truest sense, involves care and concern for others. It goes beyond self-centered desires and encompasses a genuine commitment to the well-being and happiness of others.</p><p>Both concepts challenge a narrow view of intelligence that is solely focused on individual achievement or control. Instead, they highlight the importance of cultivating a broader perspective that includes empathy, compassion, and a genuine concern for others. Intelligence, in this context, involves understanding, nurturing, and promoting the well-being and happiness of individuals and the larger interconnected systems they are part of.</p><p>By integrating the notion of care into the understanding of intelligence, both concepts emphasize the significance of ethical considerations, interconnectedness, and the promotion of positive relationships and interactions. They encourage a shift from self-centeredness to a more inclusive and compassionate perspective, recognizing the importance of fostering meaningful connections and contributing to the well-being of others.</p><p>In summary, the idea of "Intelligence as Care" aligns with the underlying principles of the Axiology of Love system, as both emphasize the interconnectedness of individuals, the importance of care and concern for others, and the cultivation of ethical intelligence that promotes the well-being and happiness of all.</p></div></div></div><div class="flex justify-between lg:block"><div class="text-xs flex items-center justify-center gap-1 self-center pt-2 !invisible"><button disabled="" class="dark:text-white disabled:text-gray-300 dark:disabled:text-gray-400"><svg stroke="currentColor" fill="none" str